T* (As we read the international news from here on the ground in China, the world appears) Tj
T* (engulfed in a storm leaving few, if any, places to hide. If last week’s widespread selling) Tj
T* (of the safest investments \(US treasuries\) is any indication, faith in the world’s safest) Tj
T* (harbor seems shaken to its core as the US sweeps the world into the vortex of its own) Tj
T* (tempest.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (In sharp contrast, an air of calm and optimism persists here in China. Last Friday, a few of) Tj
T* (us at ShoreVest attended a close friend’s IPO at the Shenzhen Stock Exchange, where) Tj
T* (excitement abounded as the ag tech company’s share price shot up. In other conversations) Tj
T* (with business and government, there is a sense of resilient confidence. While China has been) Tj
T* (incorrectly castigated in recent years as “uninvestible,” ShoreVest’s view \(as we have) Tj
T* (repeatedly written\) is that many of the misunderstood regulatory moves by Beijing were) Tj
T* (simply for the sake of long-term stability – even in preparation for this moment. Resilience) Tj
T* (and stability are what China was seeking, and on the ground that’s how it feels today \(only) Tj
T* (~3% of China's GDP comes from exports to the US, so even US tariffs have limited impact\).) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (It is heartening for China to be attracting friends and even adversaries \(e.g. Japan, South) Tj
T* (Korea\) into its orbit in their quest to hedge their bets in America’s new zero-sum game.) Tj
T* (This is exactly what we predicted would happen in our China Debt Dynamics: *United States of) Tj
T* (China* piece in December. From “China-plus-one,” the sentiment seems rapidly shifting to) Tj
T* (“America-plus-one,” in search of a large and resourceful ally as a stable trading partner) Tj
T* (and strategic anchor in a world stormed by erratic pronouncements and unstable actions.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Amidst the global economic order upheaval, an ascendant China \(already on the path to) Tj
T* (recovery from its property sector meltdown\) is being recognized once again as a potential) Tj
T* (safe and uncorrelated harbor the world seeks. The second largest economy is also the second) Tj
T* (largest importer of merchandise, offering a market for global manufacturers, including now) Tj
T* (displaced exporters to the US. As the world’s largest exporter of goods, China is also the) Tj
T* (source for key inputs \(e.g. rare earth minerals, pharmaceutical ingredients, etc.\) and) Tj
T* (high-value goods \(e.g. robots, EVs, etc.\) to fulfill demands of manufacturers and consumers) Tj
T* (alike. With fraying US trade and military alliances in Europe, many EU countries are seeking) Tj
T* (a more respectful cooperation with China.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Furthermore, with funding suspended by USAID to many developing countries, China is stepping) Tj
T* (in as a financier of last resort to help develop the global south. Just as US tariffs were) Tj
T* (indiscriminately hiked even for many poor African countries, Beijing eliminated tariffs on) Tj
T* (imports from many of the world’s least-developed countries.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Besides trade, it is becoming increasingly clear that China is an innovation hub second to) Tj
T* (none. Thriving in the face of adversity is a hallmark of China’s tech innovators \(as seen in) Tj
T* (DeepSeek, Huawei, SMIC, CATL, etc.\). In contrast to the protectionist tariff approach now) Tj
T* (used by the US administration to try to spur its domestic manufacturing, China instead uses) Tj
T* (State support and bank lending to encourage tech, biotech, green energy, agriculture and) Tj
