T* (China also increasingly appears more friendly for both education and business than the US is) Tj
T* (becoming, with rising incidents of American detention of foreign-born students and) Tj
T* (professionals and sudden cancellation of student visas.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (It is fair to say that the recent US abdication of its role as a leader of the democratic) Tj
T* (world paves the way for a multi-polar world, where China’s central government-managed) Tj
T* (approach to economic prosperity can happily coexist along with a legion of democracies. In) Tj
T* (this light, China will always remain an important global force that should not be) Tj
T* (underestimated. For global allocators, and especially those seeking all-weather strategies) Tj
T* (like private credit, ignoring China would be at one’s peril. Not only is China clearly) Tj
T* (investible \(as seen in ShoreVest’s 20+ years of success in the country\), it is likely the) Tj
T* (least correlated large market, driven by local idiosyncratic opportunities, affording a) Tj
T* (safer harbor during tumultuous times.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (In virtually every conversation we have had recently in China \(from government to business) Tj
T* (leaders, even down to taxi drivers\), the common refrain is this: “Can’t we just get back to) Tj
T* (doing win-win \(共赢\) business?” ShoreVest echoes this sentiment.) Tj
